headline: Texas Stock Exchange hires top ETF executives from Cboe, Nasdaq
summary: The Texas Stock Exchange (TSXE), still months away from winning regulatory approval to begin operations, said it hired senior exchange-traded funds executives from Cboe Global Markets and Nasdaq to win a share of trading in the $11 trillion U.S. ETF market.  It announced on Thursday that Robert Marrocco, formerly global head of ETP, or exchange-traded products, listings at Cboe Global Markets, will take on the same role at TXSE and Alison Hennessy, the former head of ETP listings at Nasdaq, will become managing director of exchange traded products.
